ggz-sdl-games
------------------------------------------
GGZ Gaming Zone SDL games

Two SDL games running in fullscreen mode have found their way into this 
package so far: the Geekgame and the OpenGL-based TTT3D, a 
three-dimensional Tic-Tac-Toe client.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-11
  ggz-client-libs-0.0.14.1-1
  libGL1-7.0.3-1
  libSDL12-1.2.13-1
  libSDL_image-1.2.6-1
  libSDL_mixer-1.2.8-1
  libSDL_ttf-2.0.9-1
  libX11_6-1.1.3-1
  libXcursor1-1.1.9-1
  libggz2-0.0.14.1-1
  libggzmod4-0.0.14.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.10-1.10.1-1
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.11-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.ggzgamingzone.org/packages/

Canonical download:
  ftp://ftp.ggzgamingzone.org/pub/ggz/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ggz-sdl-games-0.0.14.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ggz-sdl-games-0.0.14.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ggz-sdl-games-0.0.14.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ggz-sdl-games-0.0.14.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /etc/ggz/games/geekgame.dsc
  /etc/ggz/games/ggz.ttt3d.dsc
  /etc/postinstall/ggz-sdl-games.sh
  /etc/preremove/ggz-sdl-games.sh
